SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778695868
OL,3,CTriple killer Calocane shouldn't have
OL,4,Cbeen discharged to GP, inquiry hears
OL,6,FThe circumstances in which a practice
OL,7,Fwould challenge a decision to
OL,8,Fdischarge a patient to its care would
OL,9,Fbe if it were known that there was a
OL,10,F"clear and present danger to the
OL,11,Fpatient or others if that specialist
OL,12,Fcare were to be withdrawn, outside the
OL,13,Fability of primary care to manage", Dr
OL,14,FBaker's written statement said.
OL,16,FThe practice did not consider
OL,17,Fchallenging the decision because its
OL,18,Frecords "held no concerns about VC"
OL,19,Fand it entrusted the trust to "make
OL,20,Fsafe clinical decisions", it added.
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@bO]zD@IOUzD@cO]{D@_OU|D@XO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,378,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F377A1778695868
OL,3,CTriple killer Calocane shouldn't have
OL,4,Cbeen discharged to GP, inquiry hears
OL,6,FAsked by Mr Carr if, following
OL,7,FCalocane's discharge, they considered
OL,8,Fthat he was under their care for his
OL,9,Fmental health, Dr Baker said: "No,
OL,10,Fwith his diagnosis, we would clearly
OL,11,Fsee his physical health, we have a
OL,12,Fclear duty of care to offer that, but
OL,13,Fwith a diagnosis such as paranoid
OL,14,Fschizophrenia, my view is that is an
OL,15,Fenduring serious mental illness that
OL,16,Fprobably requires ongoing secondary
OL,17,Fcare so I would never put him in the
OL,18,Fcategory of being stable."
OL,26,@qD@_OUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
